- `fs n` are simple functions converging to `f`.
- We need to show that `(RCLike.ofReal ∘ NNReal.toReal ∘ ⇑(fs n)) x` tends to `(RCLike.ofReal ∘ NNReal.toReal ∘ f) x`.

The key insight is that `f` is the pointwise supremum of the sequence `fs n`. Therefore, for each `x`, `f x` is the limit of `fs n x`.

